Explanation:
Soups 111, 222 and 444 are base atomic soups. The base decompositions of the other soups are:

soup 333: {1,2}\{1, 2\}{1,2}
soup 555: {1,2,4}\{1, 2, 4\}{1,2,4}
soup 666: {1,2}\{1, 2\}{1,2} (two units of soup 222 cancel out)
soup 777: {2,4}\{2, 4\}{2,4}
soup 888: {1,4}\{1, 4\}{1,4}

For the first query, we can choose subsequences [3,4][3, 4][3,4] and [5][5][5]. The base decomposition of subsequence {3,4}\{3, 4\}{3,4} is {1,2,4}\{1, 2, 4\}{1,2,4}, which is the same as the base decomposition of soup 555.
For the last query, we can choose subsequences [6,8][6, 8][6,8] and [7][7][7]. The base decomposition of each subsequence is {2,4}\{2, 4\}{2,4}, because two units of soup 111 cancel out. You may notice that the chosen subsequences do not form a partition of all KKK given soups, since soup 555 was not used at all.
